<item>
            <title>[SOLR-801] configurable delete query  per root-entity</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-801</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Now on a full import DIH deletes &lt;b&gt;:&lt;/b&gt; which is a problem if I have different root entities .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggest having a deleteByQuery attribute for each root entity so that cleanup can issue a different query instead of &lt;b&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12405801">SOLR-801</key>
            <summary>configurable delete query  per root-entity</summary>
                <type id="2" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/newfeature.png">New Feature</type>
