                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12638441" author="hossman" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2008 00:41:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;perhaps a preFullBuildDeleteQuery and a postFullBuildDeleteQuery ... somepeople might want to delete all existing entities before starting a full build &amp;#8211; others might want to wait until after the full build to delete old stuff (anything that hasn&apos;t been updated in since NOW-1DAY for example)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12638477" author="noble.paul" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2008 05:40:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;OK .makes sense .Let us make it&lt;br/&gt;
preImportDeleteQuery and &lt;br/&gt;
postImportDeleteQuery&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;delta import also use the same query. By default delta-import does not do delete (unless clean=true is passed in request param)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12642865" author="noble.paul" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2008 06:48:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;per root-entity preImport deletes are common .while the post import delete queries are rare. So chosen to name the pre import query as deleteByQuery. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12642866" author="noble.paul" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2008 06:49:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;deleteByQuery per root entity is implemented&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12651354" author="shalinmangar" created="Thu, 27 Nov 2008 13:41:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bringing patch in sync with trunk. No other changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12667111" author="noble.paul" created="Sun, 25 Jan 2009 17:37:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Brought uptodate w/ trunck and code simplified&lt;br/&gt;
The attribute names are&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;preImportDeleteQuery&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;postImportDeleteQuery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12667115" author="shalinmangar" created="Sun, 25 Jan 2009 18:06:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 737555.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Noble!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12667185" author="shalinmangar" created="Mon, 26 Jan 2009 08:35:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Re-opening due to failed tests. I&apos;ll attach a fix shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12667187" author="shalinmangar" created="Mon, 26 Jan 2009 08:40:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for the fix:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If deleteQuery is null, call SolrWriter.doDeleteAll. Since deleteQuery is already set to &quot;* : *&quot; in execute method, it is never null.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12667189" author="shalinmangar" created="Mon, 26 Jan 2009 08:45:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 737652.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12676247" author="shalinmangar" created="Tue, 24 Feb 2009 11:20:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I encountered a NPE in case of multiple root entities when deleteQuery is not specified.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 747343.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775548" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:51:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
